<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="647" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d647">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Powell</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-10"><hi rend="italic">September 10,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 538.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 1140, of the 29th ultimo, in regard to the political situation in
                            Haiti.</p>
                        <p>Your communication to the Provisional Government advising it that this
                            Government would not recognize a paper blockade of Gonaives, St. Marc,
                            and Port de Paix, nor one imposed without due notice given, is
                            approved.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>